{
  "texts": [
    "Through recursive application of this agent to optimize its own code, they provide a proof-of-concept for self-improvement in language modelbased agents.",
    "SummaryThe upper limit of what Transformers can achieve through in-context learning remains uncertain.",
    "However, a notable achievement lies in their ability to emulate reasoning strategies and even basic machine learning algorithms.",
    "Furthermore, refining in-context learning capabilities is feasible through effective pre-training strategies.To address the limitations of modern language models, leveraging external tools and memory proves beneficial.",
    "Additionally, employing sophisticated prompting techniques enhances robustness against inadvertent reasoning errors and enables learning from experience without re-training.The comparative table presents the key results of various studies that were considered in this review (Appendix A)."
  ]
}